						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone built into the right wall of the Varāha shrine in the Veṅkaṭēs11vara temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 1808.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1730, Vibhava, Māgha, śu. 12, Monday.</hi> The <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> corresponds <hi rend="bold">to A.D. 1809, January 16.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription states that the image of Varāha was installed on the hill of Kallaḷī by Śēsha.</p>						

